      • invDigamma

        public static double invDigamma(double X)
        Returns the Inverse digamma of a given double value.

        The digamma function is the derivative of the log gamma function. It calculates the value Y > 0 for a value X such that digamma(Y) = X. This algorithm is from Paul Fackler & Harvard Univesity: http://www4.ncsu.edu/~pfackler/ http://hips.seas.harvard.edu/content/inverse-digamma-function-matlab

        Parameters:
        X - a double value.
        Returns:
        a double value Y, such as Digamma(Y) = X.
